SIMPLE: layer
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Layer
<hw>Lay"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Lay</er> to
cause to lie flat.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who, or that which,
lays.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <ety>[Prob. a corruption of <ets>lair</ets>.]</ety>
<def>That which is laid; a stratum; a bed; one thickness, course, or
fold laid over another; <as>as, a <ex>layer</ex> of clay or of sand in
the earth; a <ex>layer</ex> of bricks, or of plaster; the
<ex>layers</ex> of an onion.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A shoot or twig of a plant, not detached from the
stock, laid under ground for growth or propagation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>An artificial oyster bed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>layered</ent>⟦br⟧
